I used to give myself a LOT of credit for my marriage to @lisabilyeu. I thought, damn, man... I’m GOOD at this. And then it hit me... the statement that 80% of a successful relationship is selection. 

You have to choose the right partner. A high functioning relationship will be the greatest joy of your life - something well worth great sacrifice to protect and nurture. But a dysfunctional relationship will completely dismantle your life. 

Before you embark on the journey of rebuilding, make sure that you’re rebuilding the right relationship. If this is the right relationship - amazing! Go on in repairing. But, man... if it’s not. If you’re in a relationship with someone who has contempt for you or you have contempt for them, I advise you to face head on that this may not be the right relationship to save. 

Just keep in mind, your partner is looking at you the same way. You both have to be worth fighting for. 

For anyone out there struggling, I’m sending you good vibes and hoping that you can build a better situation for yourself - with your current partner or without them. 

But don’t think your worth is tied up in making it work. You’ve only got one shot at life, so make sure you’re building something that lifts you and those around you up. I’m sending all the love in the world. 

For @lisabilyeu ’s take on this be sure to subscribe to our Relationship Theory YouTube channel. We go deep on all of this stuff. Link in bio.

node.text:
Be legendary. I say it a lot, but what does it mean? Outside of sounding epic, it captures the idea of striving to be so great that people tell stories of your accomplishments. 

Now every legend from myth has a moral. They teach about hubris or rage or love, but at their core they show us that our weaknesses are within us, and that we must overcome them or we will fall victim to them.

As the great writer Joseph Campbell wrote in his seminal piece on mythology and storytelling The Hero With A Thousand Faces… “It is only when a man tames his own demons that he becomes the king of himself if not of the world.”

So, now when I say BE LEGENDARY, you know exactly what you must do - tame your demons and become king of yourself!

node.text:
It is easy to point to those that have achieved excellence and say, “It’s their unique build, their genetics, their upbringing, etc. that has gifted them such greatness.”

And while it is often true that they do possess innate gifts, and potentially had other advantages, what is often glossed over is their investment.

Why? Well, the effort isn’t sexy or cool. The effort is the hours spent on mobility, or in the weight room, on the track, in quiet contemplation to prepare the mind for competition. But @usainbolt or @simonebiles, or @m_phelps00 would not be the names they are if they weren’t in love with the effort.

So fall in love with the effort. Become best friends. Because it is only through the effort that true excellence can be unlocked.

🖊 @/ValaAfshar on Twitter

Is it a bird? Is it a plane? No, it’s a man putting his whole heart into one moment! 

You may not recognize him, or even care for this sport, but what is undeniable when you look at a person striving to be superhuman, is the complete and utter dedication it takes. 

Take a moment and think about the last time you poured yourself into a single instance with complete abandon. How did it feel to give it your all?

Shout out @_infinite_tucker for his winning Superman dive 🔥 via @sportscenter @secnetwork @aggietrk
